field.value:
The QueryString generated by AbstractHelper.BuildQueryString uses "&" as querystring separator, which is invalid under XML/XHTML.
I've fixed it replacing "&" by "&amp;" on my environment, but I haven't tested if it works correctly under older browsers (IE5, IE5.5).
I also don't know if it breaks ASP.NET/MonoRail querystring parsing.
Anyone want to test it?
Index: AbstractHelper.cs =================================================================== --- AbstractHelper.cs (revision 1168) +++ AbstractHelper.cs (working copy) @@ -130,7 +130,7 @@ { if (entry.Value == null) continue;
- sb.AppendFormat( "{0}={1}&", + sb.AppendFormat( "{0}={1}&amp;", UrlEncode(entry.Key.ToString()), UrlEncode(entry.Value.ToString()) ); }
